o%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F22%2Fbusiness%2Fmedia%2Fjeff-bezos-washington-post.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20past%20years%2C%20representatives%20of%20Bezos%20kept%20close%20tabs%20on%20the%20budget%2C%20but%20Bezos%20has%20recently%20taken%20a%20more%20active%20approach%20as%20the%20publication%20has%20encountered%20economic%20headwinds%20and%20internal%20dissent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20early%202021%2C%20The%20Post%20boasted%203%20million%20digital%20subscribers%2C%20fueled%20by%20the%20lightning-speed%20news%20cycles%20of%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20and%20had%20more%20than%201%2C000%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20up%20from%20about%20580%20staffers%20before%20Bezos'%20investment%20in%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20digital%20subscriptions%20now%20sit%20at%202.5%20million%2C%20and%20the%20newspaper%20has%20stumbled%20in%20boosting%20that%20figure%2C%20according%20to%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Times%20report%20noted%20that%20The%20Post%20was%20set%20to%20lose%20%24100%20million%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20two%20individuals%20with%20knowledge%20of%20The%20Post's%20financial%20situation%20who%20spoke%20to%20the%20newspaper.%20Two%20other%20individuals%20also%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20The%20Post%20was%20projected%20to%20miss%20its%20advertising%20revenue%20estimates%20for%20the%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPatty%20Stonesifer%2C%20the%20interim%20chief%20executive%20for%20The%20Post%2C%20told%20The%20Times%20that%20Bezos%20was%20thrilled%20with%20%26quot%3Bevery%20dollar%20invested%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20company.%20And%20an%20individual%20with%20knowledge%20of%20Bezos'%20vision%20for%20The%20Post%20said%20that%202023%20would%20be%20a%20%26quot%3Byear%20for%20investment%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI'm%20very%20enthusiastic%20about%20what%20we%20can%20do%20here%20at%20The%20Washington%20Post%20in%20the%20decade%20ahead%2C%26quot%3B%20Stonesifer%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BJeff's%20second%20decade%20of%20ownership%20of%20The%20Post%20should%20be%20even%20more%20exciting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Bezos%20bought%20The%20Post%20in%202013%2C%20it%20was%20the%20end%20of%20an%20era%20for%20the%20newspaper%2C%20which%20for%20generations%20had%20been%20run%20by%20the%20Graham%20family%2C%20whose%20stewardship%20saw%20the%20paper%20ascend%20to%20monumental%20heights%20with%20its%20Watergate%20and%20Pentagon%20Papers%20coverage.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBezos%20encouraged%20digital%20experimentation%20when%20he%20first%20bought%20the%20newspaper%2C%20angling%20to%20make%20The%20Post%20into%20an%20international%20powerhouse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20Bezos'%20initial%20purchase%20of%20The%20Post%2C%20his%20influence%20was%20less%20visible%20in%20the%20newsroom%2C%20according%20to%20two%20individuals%20who%20spoke%20with%20The%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20morale%20cratered%2C%20editor%20Sally%20Buzbee%20%E2%80%94%20whom%20Bezos%20had%20helped%20select%20to%20succeed%20veteran%20editor%20Marty%20Baron%20%E2%80%94%20reached%20out%20to%20the%20Amazon%20founder%20to%20discuss%20the%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%2C%20Bezos%20made%20an%20unusual%20visit%20to%20the%20newsroom%2C%20attending%20a%20morning%20meeting%20and%20later%20meeting%20with%20several%20journalists%20at%20the%20paper.%20The%20journalists%20reportedly%20spoke%20with%20Bezos%20about%20some%20larger%20newsroom%20issues%20with%20Fred%20Ryan%20%E2%80%94%20the%20newspaper's%20publisher%20%E2%80%94%20who%20in%20June%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpr%2F2023%2F06%2F12%2Ffred-ryan-publisher-ceo-announces-decision-step-down-washington-post-lead-new-civility-initiative%2F%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20would%20step%20down%20from%20his%20position%20later%20in%20the%20summer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBezos%20has%20continued%20to%20look%20ahead%20as%20he%20seeks%20to%20put%20his%20imp