3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20drastic%20changes%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20heartland%20not%20only%20threaten%20the%20country%20long-term%2C%20but%20they%20continue%20to%20present%20enormous%20challenges%20for%20troops%20seeking%20strategic%20advantages%20against%20Moscow%2C%20having%20had%20earlier%20successes%20against%20Russian%20forces%20before%20the%20mines%20began%20to%20slow%20down%20Ukraine's%20counteroffensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EWhile%20there%20are%20ongoing%20efforts%20to%20remove%20the%20mines%2C%20also%20referred%20to%20as%20unexploded%20ordnance%2C%20the%20full%20scope%20of%20the%20situation%20will%20likely%20be%20unknown%20for%20some%20time%20as%20the%20conflict%20continues.%20However%2C%20according%20to%20data%20already%20collected%20by%20the%20Ukrainian%20government%20and%20humanitarian%20mine%20clearance%20organizations%2C%20the%20direness%20of%20the%20situation%20may%20last%20for%20generations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EGreg%20Crowther%2C%20the%20director%20of%20programs%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.maginternational.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMines%20Advisory%20Group%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20nongovernmental%20organization%20that%20aids%20individuals%20affected%20by%20land%20mines%2C%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20mine%20situation%20in%20Ukraine%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fformer-special-forces-engineer-says-russian-land-mines-are-exhausting-2023-7%5C%22%3Eunlike%20anything%20seen%20in%20recent%20decades%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BThe%20sheer%20quantity%20of%20ordnance%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20just%20unprecedented%20in%20the%20last%2030%20years.%20There's%20nothing%20like%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20the%20newspaper.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globsec.org%2F%5C%22%3EGLOBSEC%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20global%20think%20tank%2C%20recently%20published%20a%20report%20revealing%20that%20about%2030%25%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20covering%20more%20than%2067%2C000%20square%20miles%2C%20had%20been%20subject%20to%20heavy%20fighting%20and%20would%20require%20thorough%20clearance%20operations.%20The%20report%20also%20detailed%20the%20lengths%20taken%20by%20Russian%20forces%20to%20make%20vast%20expanses%20of%20Ukrainian%20farmland%20either%20too%20difficult%20to%20navigate%20or%20effectively%20unusable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BTo%20date%2C%20the%20Kharkiv%20and%20Kherson%20oblasts%20remain%20the%20most%20contaminated%20regions%20of%20all%20the%20liberated%20territories%2C%20as%20Russian%20forces%20had%20been%20present%20there%20for%20a%20longer%20period%20of%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20says.%20%26quot%3BThe%20nature%20of%20the%20demining%20challenge%20is%20different%20to%20the%20pre-Feb%202022%20situation%3A%20First%2C%20fighting%20has%20been%20heavier%20and%20longer%20in%20duration%3B%20second%2C%20a%20far%20greater%20range%20of%20explosive%20ordnance%20has%20been%20deployed%2C%20and%2C%20finally%2C%20the%20area%20of%20potentially%20contaminated%20territory%20is%2010%20times%20greater.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BRussian%20troops%20are%20infamously%20creative%20in%20leaving%20mine%20traps%3A%20They%20plant%20victim-activated%20devices%20on%20animals%2C%20dead%20bodies%2C%20as%20well%20as%20double%20and%20even%20triple%20booby%20traps%20on%20roads%2C%20fields%2C%20and%20forests%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20continued.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20been%20reported%20that%20the%20Russians%20have%20also%20deliberately%20targeted%20farming%20areas%20and%20agricultural%20land%20for%20contamination%20in%20order%20to%20deny%20its%20use%20for%20future%20economic%20activity%20in%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20humanitarian%20clearance%20work%2C%20which%20is%20intricate%20and%20expensive%2C%20can%20also%20take%20a%20long%20time%20to%20complete.%20Such%20efforts%20are%20being%20employed%20around%20Kyiv%2C%20the%20capital%20city%2C%20and%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20located%20west%20of%20the%20front%20lines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EBut%20several%20experts%20told%20The%20Post%20that%20the%20amount%20of%20contaminated%20land%20in%20Ukraine%20is%20so%20massive%20that%20it%20could%20take%20close%20to%20500%20demining%20teams%20and%20757%20years%20to%20finish%20the%20work.%20And%20the%20World%20Bank%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.un.org%2Fen%2Fstory%2F2023%2F07%2F1138477%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520World%2520Bank%2520estimates%2520that%2Cmine%2520action%2520in%2520the%2520country.%5C%22%3Eestimated%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20demining%20work%20could%20exceed%20%2437%20billion%20through%202033.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C%22%20data-el%3D%5C%22text%5C%22%3EThe%20mines%20have%20also%20had%20a%20major%20effect%20on%20deminers%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highly%20trained%20individuals%20who%20are%20tasked%20with%20clearing%20unexploded%20ordnance%20%E2%80%94%20as%20they%20are%20not%20immune%20from%20the%20harm%20caused%20by%20the%20mines%20and%20booby%20traps%20laid%20down%20by%20Russian%20forces.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22null%5C%22%20data-testid%3D%5C%22drop-cap-letter%5C