ussed%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20announced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgov.texas.gov%2Fnews%2Fpost%2Foperation-lone-star-surges-border-resources-as-title-42-ends%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20surge%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20resources%20after%20the%20expiration%20of%20Title%2042%2C%20which%20he%20described%20as%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%26quot%3Blaying%20down%20the%20welcome%20mat%20to%20people%20across%20the%20entire%20world.%26quot%3B%20The%20Trump-era%20public%20health%20order%20had%20allowed%20federal%20authorities%20to%20quickly%20remove%20people%20who%20crossed%20the%20border%20illegally%2C%20without%20processing%20asylum%20claims%2C%20but%20critics%20said%20it%20broke%20international%20law%20%E2%80%94%20which%20requires%20countries%20to%20consider%20requests%20for%20asylum%20%E2%80%94%20and%20also%20encouraged%20repeat%20attempts%20to%20enter%20the%20United%20States%2C%20as%20those%20removals%20did%20not%20carry%20the%20same%20legal%20weight%20as%20a%20formal%20deportation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20order%20was%20rescinded%20in%20May%2C%20the%20number%20of%20people%20crossing%20the%20border%20illegally%20has%20dropped%20to%20the%20lowest%20rate%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbp.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fnational-media-release%2Fcbp-releases-june-2023-monthly-update%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20than%20two%20years%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECourts%20uphold%20federal%20supremacy%20on%20immigration%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHistorically%2C%20courts%20have%20rejected%20state%20efforts%20to%20regulate%20immigration%2C%20ruling%20that%20such%20authority%20lies%20exclusively%20with%20the%20federal%20government.%20And%20Texas%20ceded%20absolute%20sovereignty%20over%20its%20borders%20when%20it%20ceased%20being%20an%20independent%20republic%20in%201845.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fsupreme-court-immigration-deportation-a03ef5cc1b5468b396c0ff4688ff186d%5C%22%3Eby%20an%208-1%20margin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rejected%20an%20argument%20from%20Republican%20states%20that%20the%20president%20should%20be%20compelled%20to%20prioritize%20the%20deportation%20of%20anyone%20in%20the%20United%20States%20without%20documentation.%20Justice%20Brett%20Kavanaugh%2C%20writing%20for%20the%20majority%2C%20said%20the%20Biden%20administration%2C%20like%20its%20predecessors%2C%20%26quot%3Blacks%20the%20resources%20to%20arrest%20and%20prosecute%20every%20violator%20of%20every%20law%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20has%20the%20right%20to%20focus%20its%20deportation%20efforts%20on%20those%20convicted%20of%20other%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20%26quot%3Bdoes%20not%20give%20states%20the%20authority%20to%20carry%20out%20immigration%20enforcement%20at%20the%20border%2C%26quot%3B%20Aaron%20Reichlin-Melnick%2C%20policy%20director%20at%20the%20American%20Immigration%20Council%2C%20argued%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FReichlinMelnick%2Fstatus%2F1682453377064620037%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epost%20on%20Twitter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BPeriod.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20letter%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice%20hinted%20that%20it%20could%20take%20further%20action%20based%20on%20such%20constitutional%20arguments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas'%20actions%20%26quot%3Bviolate%20federal%20law%2C%20raise%20humanitarian%20concerns%2C%20present%20serious%20risks%20to%20public%20safety%20and%20the%20environment%2C%20and%20may%20interfere%20with%20the%20federal%20government's%20ability%20to%20carry%20out%20its%20official%20duties%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20news%20tip%3F%20Email%20this%20reporter%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Acdavis%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecdavis%40insider.com%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdi