al-elections%2Fa-65756928%5C%22%3Edrubbing%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%C2%A0country%2C%20the%20traditional%20centre-right%20Popular%20Party%20(PP)%20teamed%20up%20with%20the%20ascendant%20far-right%20party%20Vox%C2%A0to%20form%20a%20governing%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Valencian%20power-sharing%20deal%20is%20not%20unprecedented%20at%20the%20regional%20level%20in%20Spain.%20But%20after%20centre-left%20Prime%20Minister%20Pedro%20Sanchez%20called%20snap%20parliamentary%20elections%20for%20July%2023%20%E2%80%93%20elections%20were%20originally%20slated%20for%20later%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20the%20eastern%20coastal%20city%20represents%20a%20glimpse%20of%20what%20might%20happen%20on%20the%20national%20level%20if%20Sanchez%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20gamble%20goes%20awry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20four%20years%20in%20government%2C%20the%20coalition%20between%20the%20Socialists%C2%A0and%20its%20far-left%20junior%20partner%20Unidas%20Podemos%20(%E2%80%9CUnited%20We%20Can%E2%80%9D)%20could%20easily%20lose%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20final%20pre-Election%20Day%20opinion%20polls%20showed%20PP%20with%20a%20comfortable%20lead%20over%20the%20Socialists%20but%20short%20of%20an%20outright%20majority%20without%20Vox%E2%80%99s%20support%2C%20according%20to%20the%20news%20agency%20Reuters.%20Even%20then%2C%20the%20two%20parties%20could%20still%20fall%20short%20of%20the%20parliamentary%20seats%20needed%20to%20form%20a%20right-wing%20coalition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20especially%20true%20because%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20two%20major%20parties%20has%20closed%20in%20recent%20weeks.%20Sumar%2C%20a%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspains-left-proposes-20000-payments-for-young-adults%2Fa-66165333%5C%22%3Eleft-wing%20alliance%3C%2Fa%3E%20which%20includes%20Unidas%20Podemos%2C%20is%20running%20neck-and-neck%20with%20Vox%C2%A0and%20could%20potentially%C2%A0team%20up%20with%20the%20Socialists%20to%20give%20Sanchez%20a%20second%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVox%20poised%20to%20play%20kingmaker%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20just%20a%20day%20to%20go%20until%20Election%20Day%2C%20the%20outcome%20remains%20to%20be%20seen.%20But%20if%20Spain%20indeed%20swings%20to%20the%20right%2C%20it%20may%20well%20follow%20recent%20electoral%20trends%20in%20other%20European%20countries%20like%20Italy%2C%20Finland%2C%20Sweden%20and%20Greece%20%E2%80%93%20all%20of%20which%20saw%20an%20upswing%20in%20support%20for%20right-wing%20parties%20in%20recent%20national%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVox%2C%20which%20was%20founded%20in%202013%20and%20first%20gained%20seats%20in%20the%20Spanish%20parliament%20in%202019%2C%20has%20instrumentalised%20its%20hardline%20positions%20on%20social%20issues%20and%20immigration%20to%20steadily%20build%20its%20support%20in%20recent%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Valencia%E2%80%99s%20coastal%20promenade%2C%20some%20passersby%20were%20clearly%20alarmed%20by%20the%20prospect.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20totally%20insane%20%E2%80%93%20the%20worst%20thing%20that%20could%20happen%20to%20this%20country%2C%E2%80%9D%20one%20woman%20with%20strong%20thoughts%20on%20a%20PP-Vox%20national%20government%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98s%20Jan-Philipp%20Scholz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20who%20oppose%20Vox%C2%A0fear%20the%20ultraconservative%C2%A0approach%20it%20takes%20to%20social%20issues.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20want%20to%20scrap%20the%20abortion%20law%3B%C2%A0they%20want%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20the%20euthanasia%20law%3B%20they%20say%20that%20gender%20violence%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%E2%80%9D%C2%A0a%20younger%20woman%20from%20Madrid%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%E2%80%9CIt%20all%20makes%20me%20really%20scared.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sanchez-led%20government%20has%20pushed%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fspain-passes-laws-on-trans-rights-abortion-menstrual-leave%2Fa-64731685%5C%22%3Ea%20string%20of%20socially%20progressive%2